    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "That makes sense, but it sounds pretty risky. Are there any specific types of mistakes or situations that would most likely trigger this? Like, is there anything 'hidden' in the wording that I should be on the lookout for that might bite me later? I just want to know if there are any sneaky ways this could be used against me.",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The wording is quite broad, which is where the risk lies, as it covers \"any negligent or more culpable act or omission.\" This means if the Client can prove your mistake was careless or intentionally wrong, you could be liable. Be wary of vague deliverables; if your work is incomplete or flawed, they might argue it's a breach. It's always best to clarify expectations before starting, ensuring your scope of work is rock solid.",
      "source": "target",
