    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Okay, so it's basically about how much they can claim against me if something goes wrong. I'm worried about these \"hidden\" costs though. For example, if they hire a really expensive law firm because of a mistake I made, am I on the hook for all of that? Is there a way these clauses can feel a bit predatory or like they're waiting for me to fail?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Yes, you are generally on the hook for the \"reasonable attorneys' fees\" if your mistake triggers the clause, which can be a massive, unexpected cost. These clauses can certainly feel predatory because they transfer almost all the legal risk onto the freelancer. To protect yourself, you should try to negotiate a cap on your liability or limit what types of claims you are responsible for. For instance, you could ask to exclude claims arising from the Client's own negligence.",
      "source": "target",
